Anonymous Fri 08 Mar 2024 22:33:00 No.63875613 Report
Quoted By:
>>63875270
>Problems with the setting
Nigga there are plot holes in actual human history. As long as it's reasonable enough to make sense while reading, you'll be fine.
Chances are that if you're spending more than an hour on world building, you have more than enough details for it to look good, and any errant details to be dismissed with a one liner.
>Meaningless relationship
I mean, why do real relationships happen? There's really only three reasons:
A, (the most common) they are both looking for a romantic partner, and/or find each other sexually attractive enough to make an effort to be together.
B, (this one yields the strongest, and imo cutest relationships) they are in proximity by circumstance, and genuinely enjoy each other's company as if they were good friends.
C, (tends to be less romantic, but always a strong bond) they work together, and develop an intense professional respect that slowly turns to friendship.
Just pick one based on how your characters act.
>Hotheaded young man? Option A easily.
>Average joe thrust into a new situation or job? B is good.
>Socially retarded nerd character? C fits him.
